snippet: The man, a Kenyan of Somali origin known as Ikrimah, was not captured, and there is as yet no evidence that he was killed in the firefight on the Somali coast early Saturday.
abstract: Target of failed American commando raid in Horn of Africa is identified as Abdikadir Mohamed Abdikadir, Kenyan of Somali origin often referred to as Ikrimah; Abdikadir, who is thought to be one of Shabab militant group’s top planners for attacks beyond its base in Somalia, was not captured and there is no evidence that he was killed in firefight.

byline.original: By NICHOLAS KULISH, ERIC SCHMITT and MARK MAZZETTI
byline.contributor: Nicholas Kulish reported from Nairobi, Kenya; Eric Schmitt from San Francisco, and Mark Mazzetti from Madrid. Josh Kron contributed reporting from Mombasa, Kenya.

lead_paragraph: The man, a Kenyan of Somali origin known as Ikrimah, was not captured, and there is as yet no evidence that he was killed in the firefight on the Somali coast early Saturday.
